# .trivyignore — Accepted risks with documented justification.
# https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/#trivyignore

# EC2 security group — unrestricted egress is required for the instance to reach
# AWS SSM Agent endpoints, GHCR, Helm chart repos, and OS update mirrors.
# Locking egress to specific IPs would break SSM Session Manager access.
AVD-AWS-0104

# Terraform state S3 bucket — SSE-S3 (AES256) is sufficient for TF state.
# CMK rotation adds operational overhead (key deletion can brick state permanently).
AVD-AWS-0132

# Public subnet assigns public IPs — this is a single-node design where the EC2
# instance must be reachable by Cloudflare. The EIP overrides the auto-assigned IP.
AVD-AWS-0164

# Redis Bitnami subchart configmaps — health check scripts reference password env
# vars ($REDIS_PASSWORD_FILE) to test liveness; they do not store the password value.
# These templates are in a vendored third-party chart we do not control.
AVD-KSV-0109

# EC2 user_data (cloud-init.yaml) — Trivy flags `adminPassword="${GRAFANA_PASS}"` as a
# hardcoded credential. The actual value is fetched from SSM at runtime:
#   GRAFANA_PASS=$(aws ssm get-parameter --name /meridian/grafana/admin-password --with-decryption ...)
# No literal password is present in the file or the rendered user_data.
AVD-AWS-0029

# gcr.io/distroless/python3-debian12:nonroot — Kerberos libs (libkrb5, libgssapi-krb5-2,
# libk5crypto3, libkrb5support0) ship version 1.20.1-2+deb12u4; Debian patched in deb12u5.
# The distroless image has not yet been rebuilt with the new packages. We cannot update OS
# packages in a distroless image (no shell, no apt). Meridian does not use Kerberos
# authentication — this CVE (integer underflow DoS) is not reachable. Remove this
# suppression once Google rebuilds distroless/python3-debian12:nonroot with deb12u5.
CVE-2026-40356

# gcr.io/distroless/python3-debian12:nonroot — Python 3.11 packages (libpython3.11-minimal,
# libpython3.11-stdlib, python3.11-minimal) ship version 3.11.2-6+deb12u6; Debian patched
# in deb12u7. The distroless image has not yet been rebuilt with the new packages.
# This CVE (http.client read-buffering DoS) is not reachable: Meridian uses httpx and
# asyncio for all HTTP calls, not the stdlib http.client module. Remove once distroless
# rebuilds with deb12u7.
CVE-2025-13836
